mmon.  See also  Alun ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":38,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":47,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Alan de Columbers was born in 1177, in Hale, Lancashire, England, his father, William de Columbers, was 26 and his mother, Mary de Holland, was 24. He married Cecily de Waleton about 1200. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1235, at the age of 58, and was buried in Preston, Lancashire, England."},"et":{"1177–1235":"1177–1235","1181–1230":"1181–1230","1201–1298":"1201–1298","1151–1177":"1151–1177","1153–1181":"1153–1181","about 1170":"umbes 1170","1230":"1230","1153":"1153","1151":"1151","1181":"1181","1215":"1215","1235":"1235","1224":"1224","Abt 1200":"umbes 1200","1201":"1201","1177":"1177","1298":"1298","about 1177":"umbes 1177","Hale, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Hale, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hale, Lancashire, England":"Hale, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Greyfriars Church of Preston, Preston, Lancashire, England":"Preston, Lancashire, England","Hales, Lancashire, England":"Hal